MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE MOUNT RUSHMORE SOUTH DAKOTA 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  BATTLE CREEK #1 (E; #460591) IS LOCATED OUTSIDE OF THE MOUNT RUSHMORE NATIONAL MEMORIAL BOUNDARY AND IS APPROXIMATELY THREE MILES EAST OF KEYSTONE BEFORE GOING UNDER HIGHWAY 40 AT FDR 330.  SOME FACTORS THAT INFLUENCE THIS SITE'S WATER QUALITY ARE THE FOLLOWING: 1) CONSTRUCTION AND STORM RUNOFF FROM KEYSTONE; 2) OLD MINE TAILINGS; AND 3) LIVESTOCK GRAZING.  THESE FACTORS CREATE TREND PROBLEMS SUCH AS HIGH WATER TEMPERATURE; HIGH FECAL COLIFORM COUNTS; HIGH TOTAL SUSPENDED SOLIDS; AND HIGH AMMONIA CONCENTRATIONS.  FOR THE YEAR OF 1988; SPECIFIC DATES WERE NOT INCLUDED IN THE DATA SET; THEREFORE; THE 15TH OF THE MONTH WAS CHOSEN.  DATA WERE FROM THE REGIONAL HYDROLOGIST AT USDAFOREST SERVICE; BLACK HILLS NATIONAL FOREST; RR 2 BOX 200; CUSTER SD 57730 (TEL. 6056732251).  DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY LISA DUMMER; NPSWRD; 1201 OAK RIDGE DR SUITE 250; FORT COLLINS CO 80525 (TEL. 9702253516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: SPRING CREEK NEAR THREE FORKS UNDER HWY 16
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE HILL CITY SD 7.5 MINUTE SERIES (TOPO.) QUADRANGLE.  THIS SPRING CREEK SITE (#460581) IS LOCATED OUTSIDE OF THE MOUNT RUSHMORE NATIONAL MEMORIAL BOUNDARY AND IS NEAR THREE FORKS UNDER HWY 16.  DURING CONSTRUCTION ON HWY 16 AT THREE FORKS; THE STATION WAS MOVED TO 0.5 MILES ABOVE SHERIDAN LAKE RESERVOIR.  AFTER CONSTRUCTION; THE STATION WAS MOVED BACK TO THE CURRENT LOCATION.  SOME FACTORS THAT INFLUENCE THIS SITE'S WATER QUALITY ARE THE FOLLOWING: 1) CONSTRUCTION OF LAKE MITCHELL; 2) SEEPAGE OF WASTES AND RUNOFF FROM ROADS USED BY INDUSTRY AND RESIDENCES NEXT TO THE CREEK; 3) AN UPSTREAM LUMBER COMPANY; AND 4) A 1979 FUEL SPILL.  FOR THE YEAR OF 1988; SPECIFIC DATES WERE NOT INCLUDED IN THE DATA SET; THEREFORE; THE 15TH WAS CHOSEN.  DATA WERE FROM THE REGIONAL HYDROLOGIST AT USDAFOREST SERVICE; BLACK HILLS NATIONAL FOREST; RR 2 BOX 200; CUSTER SD 57730 (TEL. 6056732251). DATA WERE PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY LISA DUMMER; NPSWRD; 1201 OAK RIDGE DR SUITE 250; FORT COLLINS CO 80525 (TEL. 9702253516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM
